R7.13
a find the location of a given value
b sort an array
c create an array containing random values in a specified range

R7.15
Parallel arrays are arrays of the same length where corresponding elements
contain related data. They can be easily avoided by making a class that stores
all desired fields then making an array of objects of that class type.

R7.18
b true
d false in the sense that once you declare the ArrayList as a specific type
it can only hold values of that type. ArrayLists also can't store values of
primitive type.